#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.29"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.29:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.29:0.2"
msgid "3. Sabbavagga "
msgstr "3. All "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 29. Addhabhūtasutta → andhabhūtasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3) | andhabhūtam (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.29:0.3"
msgid "29. Addhabhūtasutta "
msgstr "29. Oppressed "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.21, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.29:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn35.29:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

msgctxt "sn35.29:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: addhabhūtaṃ → andhabhūtaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.29:1.4"
msgid "“sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, addhabhūtaṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, all is oppressed. "

msgctxt "sn35.29:1.5"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ addhabhūtaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is the all that is oppressed? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.29:1.6"
msgid "Cakkhu, bhikkhave, addhabhūtaṃ, rūpā addhabhūtā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ addhabhūtaṃ, cakkhusamphasso addhabhūto, yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi addhabhūtaṃ. "
msgstr "The eye is oppressed. Sights are oppressed. Eye consciousness is oppressed. Eye contact is oppressed. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact is also oppressed. "

msgctxt "sn35.29:1.7"
msgid "Kena addhabhūtaṃ? "
msgstr "Oppressed by what? "

msgctxt "sn35.29:1.8"
msgid "‘Jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi addhabhūtan’ti vadāmi … pe … "
msgstr "Oppressed by the fires of greed, hate, and delusion. Oppressed by rebirth, old age, and death, by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.29:1.9"
msgid "jivhā addhabhūtā, rasā addhabhūtā, jivhāviññāṇaṃ addhabhūtaṃ, jivhāsamphasso addhabhūto, yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi addhabhūtaṃ. "
msgstr "The ear … nose … tongue … "

msgctxt "sn35.29:1.10"
msgid "Kena addhabhūtaṃ? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.29:1.11"
msgid "‘Jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi addhabhūtan’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.29:1.12"
msgid "Kāyo addhabhūto … pe … "
msgstr "body … "

msgctxt "sn35.29:1.13"
msgid "mano addhabhūto, dhammā addhabhūtā, manoviññāṇaṃ addhabhūtaṃ, manosamphasso addhabhūto, yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi addhabhūtaṃ. "
msgstr "mind is oppressed. Thoughts are oppressed. Mind consciousness is oppressed. Mind contact is oppressed. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact is also oppressed. "

msgctxt "sn35.29:1.14"
msgid "Kena addhabhūtaṃ? "
msgstr "Oppressed by what? "

msgctxt "sn35.29:1.15"
msgid "‘Jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi addhabhūtan’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Oppressed by greed, hate, and delusion. Oppressed by rebirth, old age, and death, by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.29:1.16"
msgid "Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati … pe … "
msgstr "Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.29:1.17"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati. "
msgstr "They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body … mind … painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.29:1.18"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati, virāgā vimuccati, vimuttasmiṃ ‘vimuttam’iti ñāṇaṃ hoti, "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.29:1.19"
msgid "‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.29:1.20"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

